SIMPLE: senile
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Senile
<hw>Se"nile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>senilis</ets>, from <ets>senex</ets>, gen. <ets>senis</ets>, old,
an old man: cf. F. <ets>s⟦eacute⟧nile</ets>. See <er>Senior</er>.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to old age; proceeding from, or characteristic of,
old age; affected with the infirmities of old age; <as>as,
<ex>senile</ex> weakness</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Senile</xex> maturity
of judgment.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Senile gangrene</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a form
of gangrene occuring particularly in old people, and caused usually by
insufficient blood supply due to degeneration of the walls of the
smaller arteries.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Senility</ent>⟦br⟧
